  "why": "The paper demonstrates cross-model transferability by reusing fault-inducing inputs discovered via fuzzing one model (the 32-bit model) to reveal disagreements in another model (the 16-bit quantized version). However, the fuzzing design does not include explicit mechanisms aimed at discovering transferable attacks (e.g., using surrogate models to guide mutation); instead it uses the activations of the model under test as its coverage signal. Therefore the work shows transferability experimentally but does not incorporate explicit design choices to promote transferable attack discovery.",
